I’ve decided to post more everyday photos, especially now that I’m shooting all the time with the new camera. Hope you all like them! 

#leicam11 #leica #priime

We had one of those types of shoots where everything was feeling right. What a wonderful time exploring and shooting with @kendrasato in this beautiful space. Lots more photos to go (if you didn’t see my story dump of photos, there’s so many).

I used my Leica M11 paired with the Leica Summilux 50mm black chrome. While I did miss shooting 35mm and 85mm, I’m beginning to understand the beauty of this focal length. 

#priime #leicam11 #leica #summilux50mm #marincountyciviccenter

It’s been great shooting with the #LeicaM11. Not only is the camera technically great and full of character, but the way it’s forcing me to shoot is rewarding and satisfying. 

Also, it’s too easy to get awesome shots with @kendrasato in such a cool place. That combined with the more intentional shooting made post-processing quick and it felt a bit like cheating :) Quick #priime style, slight nudging of horizon, and maybe a touch on shadows and that’s all I needed. 

#leica #marincountyciviccenter

Lines on lines with @kendrasato. It’s too much fun exploring and shooting with the ever energetic Kendra. 

We got so many good shots, not sure if I’ll ever be done posting from this shoot. Good news is, there’s another shoot to come soon!

Brought my favorite model @keamoro to shoot golden hour with my new lens today! Epic light on Mount Tamalpais. Tam never disappoints. 

New lens: Leica Summilux 50mm FLE II

#leica #leicam11 #leicasummilux50mm #myleicaphoto #priime #whiteswissshepherd #bergerblancsuisse

Golden hour layers! 

Captured this shot as @keamoro and I tried to make our way to a spot above the Robin Williams Tunnel, but there was a No Pets sign towards the end, so we had to turn back. At least I got this on our way 🥰

#priime #myleicaphoto #leica #leicam11 #leicasummilux50mm

I had all the intention of selling my Summilux Black Chrome 50mm because I got the new Summilux FLE II, but then it went and got me this shot. I was shooting the same scene with both lenses, hoping that one would really outshine the other and help me make a decision, but the light was changing so much that this was my pick of the day, and honestly the black chrome lens just feels so good to use. I’ll give at least another week to make a decision. While it would be great to keep both, I want fewer choices to work with and go all in on one. (My wallet would be happier too). 

Photography hasn’t really been about the gear for me as much in the past 10-ish years, but the Leica M system has now made me reconsider not just how the images look, but how it feels when taking the photo. I can’t say enough about how the M system has changed my photography, spurred a new sense of inspiration and motivation, and even new found joy in it all. 

I feel silly and almost hypocritical, because I was always about my tiny powerful Sony RX1R2 and my ancient Nikon DSLRs, but now I totally get it. There are some cameras that are just the right feel, and the Leica M11 is exactly that for me. 

Exploring the fun lens options has also been quite the experience. Old lenses, new lenses, all have different characteristics, imperfections, and qualities that change from one copy to another. It’s just all too fun.

Have you found that one camera that just feels so right for you?

Also, Mount Tam’s watershed side is dog friendly (on leash), so we went on that side. Yes, I took @keamoro ‘s collar/leash off for this shot, but she didn’t move from here the whole time until I released her when I put her leash back on. I’m all about respecting the rules around dogs, they’re there for a reason, and the only way for dogs to continue to have access is people adhering as much as they can. 

#priime #leica #myleicaphoto #leicam11 #leica50summilux #whiteswissshepherd #bergerblancsuisse

Presenting: the magic of a cloudy day and a camp shower. 

I admire the resolve and strength of anyone who sprays themselves down with cold water on a windy chilly San Francisco evening, and pulls off these kinds of looks. That would be @kendrasato. 💪🏻

Shot with the Leica M11 + Summilux 50mm FLE II 

#leica #leicam11 #priime #myleicaphoto

I took advantage of the flowers that are still blooming around Crissy Fields to use as some soft framing of the iconic Golden Gate Bridge. There was beautiful fog coming in and it diffused the sunset just enough to create a really soft golden hour today. I wanted to shoot a bit closer to wide open to really soften everything up with this lens, and it really created a special mood. This was shot at f/1.8 on my 50mm Summilux FLE II. It could stop down to 1.4 but I didn’t want to get down that far. These two shots were at slightly different angles and just a few minutes apart. I actually like the landscape orientation version a bit more, but it isn’t presented on IG as well. 

Days like this make me so grateful, where I can just go a little ways from home after work to enjoy such beautiful views. 

#priime #leica #myleicaphoto #leicam11 #leicasummilux50mm

What a great weekend to cap off 2023 and welcome in the new year of 2024. I’ve been recently inspired by all the parallels of the ocean and life’s ongoing timeline, and seeing one surfer leaving the water and another one entering just seemed so fitting for this new year. 

Happy new year everyone!

#leica #leicam11 #leicasummilux50mm #priime

I ended the 2023 year with the start of production of a new documentary film on @dideeds, the goalkeeper for @weareangelcity, photographer, coffee maker, and all around amazing person. I’ve been working on and planning this new production company, making it a goal to begin production and starting this amazing journey of humanizing women professional athletes, nurturing a healthy and strong fanbase, through accessible and beautiful short documentaries. 

It was amazing working with the crew of @joe.pierce as the DP, @sophia_morocco as the AC, and all of us pitching in with seamless collaboration. 

Excited for more filming soon, more story writing and creative from our screenwriter @kimakimberlin, and all the crew we’ll be bringing on board soon enough. 

#noxsky @noxskyco #filmmaking #soccer @nwsl

I started off the new year with a sunrise hike with @tonycross.

Happy new year!
